== 4. exd5 · Exchange variation ==
White transposes into a variant of the French exchange variation with the moves Nc3 and ...Bb4 interposed. Black's best response remains '''4...exd5''', but '''4...Qxd5!?''' is possible and has been attempted as a way to get the opponent out of theory<ref>https://www.chessgames.com/perl/explorer?node=284403&move=4.5</ref>.

Despite being similar to the exchange French, the exchange Winawer is a lot less prone to drawn positions. White usually provokes Bxc3 with a3, leading to an asymmetrical pawn structure after bxc3.

